<item>
            <title>[JCR-436] InvalidQueryException thrown for a SQL query using WHERE CONTAINS(., &apos;someword&apos;)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-436</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The following SQL query:&lt;br/&gt;
SELECT * FROM es:document WHERE CONTAINS(., &amp;#39;software&amp;#39;)&lt;br/&gt;
throws an InvalidQueryException exception.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
javax.jcr.query.InvalidQueryException: Encountered &amp;quot;.&amp;quot; at line 1, column 42.&lt;br/&gt;
Was expecting one of:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;BY&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;IN&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;OR&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;IS&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;AND&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;LIKE&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;NULL&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;FROM&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;ORDER&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;WHERE&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;SELECT&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;BETWEEN&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;*&amp;quot; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;REGULAR_IDENTIFIER&amp;gt; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;DELIMITED_IDENTIFIER&amp;gt; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
This syntax seems correct according to the latest jcr spec (1.0.1).&lt;br/&gt;
Using an asterisk (*) instead of a dot (.) as the first parameter of CONTAINS() works fine.</description>
