                    <comment id="12414001" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 31 May 2006 16:25:49 +0100"  >This is a leftover from an unreleased version of the JCR spec. Unfortunately the relevant test case is also broken. Both is now fixed. Jackrabbit still allows to use the * in the contains function to remain somewhat backward compatible with previously released jackrabbit versions, even though this is not correct according to the spec.&lt;br/&gt;
